about the fact the game's gonna close down

93
00:05:02,695 --> 00:05:05,079
and you are gonna have to deal with this fact

94
00:05:05,159 --> 00:05:06,561
that some people are gonna feel

95
00:05:06,601 --> 00:05:08,303
they've been made a fool of a little bit.

96
00:05:08,343 --> 00:05:09,725
That's something you're gonna have to address.

97
00:05:11,279 --> 00:05:13,441
And get it together before you speak.

98
00:05:13,521 --> 00:05:15,522
I cannot stress that enough.

99
00:05:15,562 --> 00:05:17,604
That's really what is gonna make the difference.

100
00:05:17,664 --> 00:05:20,146
If you're thoughtful in the way that you

101
00:05:20,706 --> 00:05:23,729
conduct this process, it's going to change,

102
00:05:24,229 --> 00:05:27,031
it's gonna make the outcome much more positive.

103
00:05:27,532 --> 00:05:29,413
People are gonna feel that you cared,

104
00:05:29,753 --> 00:05:32,055
you cared enough to have things be coordinated

105
00:05:32,215 --> 00:05:32,976
in this end phase.

106
00:05:35,775 --> 00:05:40,518
So at the beginning of any, when a closure is planned,

107
00:05:40,538 --> 00:05:43,180
you need to put together a closure timeline.

108
00:05:43,260 --> 00:05:45,982
So some things to really think about when you're putting that

109
00:05:46,002 --> 00:05:49,044
together are that the communication is synced

110
00:05:49,104 --> 00:05:49,945
across channels.

111
00:05:50,065 --> 00:05:54,888
So that's social media, forums, official, unofficial,

112
00:05:55,308 --> 00:05:57,890
English language, non-English.

113
00:05:58,690 --> 00:06:03,233
All channels need to have this closure announcement made

114
00:06:03,373 --> 00:06:04,494
in a way that is synced.

115
00:06:05,628 --> 00:06:09,110
You also need to make sure that your PR, customer service,

116
00:06:09,250 --> 00:06:10,871
marketing are all on board.

117
00:06:10,951 --> 00:06:14,893
Because as you know, as far as your players,

118
00:06:14,913 --> 00:06:18,115
your customers are concerned, it doesn't matter who's speaking.

119
00:06:18,415 --> 00:06:19,135
It's your game.

120
00:06:19,275 --> 00:06:21,656
Internally, sometimes we start to think, oh, that's PR,

121
00:06:21,676 --> 00:06:22,297
that's marketing.

122
00:06:22,317 --> 00:06:23,457
But they don't care.

123
00:06:23,477 --> 00:06:25,478
If somebody in marketing is saying one thing

124
00:06:25,518 --> 00:06:28,240
or customer service saying another, it's confusing.

125
00:06:28,280 --> 00:06:32,282
And it gives an impression that you're not

126
00:06:32,322 --> 00:06:34,443
being thoughtful about how you get this information out.

127
00:06:35,646 --> 00:06:40,408
The other thing is really that everyone knows when and what to say internally at

128
00:06:40,468 --> 00:06:44,929
your company, even people who aren't really typically client facing all the time.

129
00:06:45,309 --> 00:06:49,011
Everybody, because of social media or just really because of the way that people

130
00:06:49,091 --> 00:06:52,492
interact and communicate, they are going to be talking with people about what's

131
00:06:52,532 --> 00:06:57,574
going on and you need to have a time when they are given a direct message and

132
00:06:57,634 --> 00:07:00,895
really they know what the company line is as far as what's going on.

133
00:07:02,172 --> 00:07:07,175
And one thing really I need to stress, which it can be overlooked, unfortunately,

134
00:07:07,415 --> 00:07:10,857
is that the registration is disabled by the team.

135
00:07:10,937 --> 00:07:14,639
So as soon as you make the announcement that the closure is going to happen,

136
00:07:14,899 --> 00:07:17,841
you have to make sure that no more people can join and

137
00:07:17,881 --> 00:07:18,561
play your game.

138
00:07:18,842 --> 00:07:20,783
That looks really bad if you forget that step.

139
00:07:22,602 --> 00:07:29,108
messaging so tailored to the channel and that all of the roads are going to lead to your closure FAQ and I'm going to talk a

140
00:07:29,148 --> 00:07:36,375
little bit more about the closure FAQ later, but you need to make sure that your messaging is in line with

141
00:07:37,396 --> 00:07:41,720
with your community. So as part of your closure plan, you're also just going to put together something that

142
00:07:42,807 --> 00:07:46,271
if you don't already have it, catalogs, who's in charge of,

143
00:07:46,431 --> 00:07:47,932
and what all your channels are.

144
00:07:48,213 --> 00:07:49,914
Again, official and unofficial,

145
00:07:49,975 --> 00:07:53,398
because fan sites on Facebook can be just as powerful,

146
00:07:53,578 --> 00:07:56,221
or even more powerful, than your own official sites.

147
00:07:56,841 --> 00:07:58,823
And when you tailor the messaging,

148
00:07:59,564 --> 00:08:02,405
The more personal you make it, the more it's going to have an impact.

149
00:08:02,505 --> 00:08:07,967
For example, if you have a group of Russian folks that meet up at a bar and

150
00:08:08,067 --> 00:08:11,569
they always meet up at a certain time, drink a certain beer, whatever,

151
00:08:11,969 --> 00:08:15,570
you reference that beer when you are making this closure announcement.

152
00:08:15,670 --> 00:08:18,911
Just every little thing that you can do to really show people that it's personal,

153
00:08:18,971 --> 00:08:22,273
and it is some big corporate branded messaging,

154
00:08:22,513 --> 00:08:24,533
it's going to make the impact that much better.

155
00:08:27,188 --> 00:08:33,230
So some key points to hit in the Closure FAQ are why, when,

156
00:08:34,090 --> 00:08:37,811
what about all my stuff, what now, and can we still talk?

157
00:08:37,971 --> 00:08:38,991
So why?

158
00:08:39,071 --> 00:08:40,152
You're going to have to address it.

159
00:08:40,252 --> 00:08:42,232
People are going to ask, why is this happening?

160
00:08:42,372 --> 00:08:46,253
Now, you can't always be exactly direct about what's going on.

161
00:08:46,293 --> 00:08:47,513
You can't give them financials.

162
00:08:47,573 --> 00:08:49,074
But it's something you're going to have to address.

163
00:08:49,114 --> 00:08:50,374
They want to know why it's happening.

164
00:08:51,249 --> 00:08:54,111
When it's going to happen and you want to put time zone,

165
00:08:54,131 --> 00:08:55,431
you want to put exact time.

166
00:08:55,531 --> 00:08:57,913
Again, you want people all around the world to know

167
00:08:57,953 --> 00:08:59,954
that you aren't just thinking about West Coast US

168
00:08:59,994 --> 00:09:00,914
when you put this time up.

169
00:09:00,974 --> 00:09:03,435
You are thinking that people need to know

170
00:09:03,515 --> 00:09:05,136
what it is in their own time zone.

171
00:09:06,697 --> 00:09:08,018
What's going to happen to my stuff?

172
00:09:08,038 --> 00:09:08,978
Now that's a big one.

173
00:09:09,258 --> 00:09:12,140
There's in-game currency that people have invested,

174
00:09:12,280 --> 00:09:12,980
time and money.

175
00:09:13,280 --> 00:09:15,061
You have to have a plan laid out

176
00:09:15,121 --> 00:09:17,983
as far as what is going to happen and in what time.

177
00:09:19,701 --> 00:09:30,831
What now? This is when you have to be a little bit careful with if you have other games you can push people to the other games but you want to not come across as too salesy or marketingy, especially at a time when people are feeling bad.

178
00:09:30,851 --> 00:09:33,353
So it's something to be careful about.

179
00:09:33,934 --> 00:09:37,817
And then can we still talk? How long can people keep talking with you?

180
00:09:38,718 --> 00:09:40,139
through the channels that they currently are?

181
00:09:40,219 --> 00:09:41,900
When does it switch over to customer service?

182
00:09:41,940 --> 00:09:43,281
Do you even have that option?

183
00:09:43,722 --> 00:09:46,283
These are things that you need to outline.

184
00:09:46,704 --> 00:09:50,046
This is not a complete version of FAQ,

185
00:09:50,066 --> 00:09:53,248
but just minimize so that you can get the gist of it.

