00:10:01,655 --> 00:10:06,376
The tone, I used to work for Lego on the Lego Universe game,

190
00:10:06,416 --> 00:10:07,937
so of course in that game,

191
00:10:08,177 --> 00:10:09,777
when we were closing down that game,

192
00:10:10,397 --> 00:10:13,878
we spoke to people from the point of view

193
00:10:13,898 --> 00:10:16,619
that they were children, mostly children playing this game.

194
00:10:16,659 --> 00:10:19,359
You have to keep that tone that you had otherwise

195
00:10:19,539 --> 00:10:22,980
in your community and carry it over into the Closure FAQ.

196
00:10:23,420 --> 00:10:25,121
Again, pushing people to other games.

197
00:10:25,801 --> 00:10:28,742
And then disabled comments is really important.

198
00:10:28,942 --> 00:10:30,882
You're gonna have plenty of spaces.

199
00:10:31,783 --> 00:10:35,386
online, again, social media, your forums, other forum topics, etc.

200
00:10:35,426 --> 00:10:37,668
Where people can discuss what's going on.

201
00:10:37,708 --> 00:10:40,510
So this is not about stifling conversation.

202
00:10:40,931 --> 00:10:43,493
But you wanna have one place where it is pristine,

203
00:10:43,533 --> 00:10:46,536
where you have exactly the message that is coming from your company.

204
00:10:46,976 --> 00:10:49,658
Which you can change if you need to later on, but

205
00:10:49,939 --> 00:10:52,701
where there's no distracting comments coming in about people.

206
00:10:53,402 --> 00:10:56,347
who are saying what is up there is wrong,

207
00:10:56,407 --> 00:10:57,849
or arguing about it, or whatever.

208
00:10:57,909 --> 00:10:59,431
That can go on in other spaces,

209
00:10:59,912 --> 00:11:01,114
but in your closure FAQ,

210
00:11:01,134 --> 00:11:03,117
you want that to be completely controlled by you.

211
00:11:05,534 --> 00:11:10,237
So we've got some examples of what I think are FAQs that are done right, and also this

